The paper presents a data structure to efficiently answer cumulative queries on trajectories of moving objects. This involves storing and representing information about the duration and length of homogeneous segments of trajectories. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG).
